  "texts": [
    "ANNs is the subfield of ML which consists of algorithms inspired by the structure and the function of the neuronal networks of the human brain.",
    "As already outlined, prominent examples of ANNs are the DL models, i.e., multi-layer perceptrons, which are very popular due to their scaling ability.",
    "Specifically, their performance, measured as any measure of accuracy in unseen test data, tends to increase with input training data volume increases.",
    "The increasing accuracy of ANNs contrasts with traditional ML models that reach a plateau in performance even when very large volumes of training data are used.",
    "Another great advantage of deep neural networks over traditional ML models is their ability to perform automatic feature extraction from raw data."
  ],
